            // such as handling render targets, or setting up any needed state.

            SDL_SetRenderDrawColor(sdlRenderer, 255, 255, 255, 255); // Set the color used for drawing operations (Rect, Line and Clear)
            SDL_RenderClear(sdlRenderer);                            // Clear the current rendering target with the drawing color
            // Here, you would render your game's entities, textures, etc.
            SDL_RenderPresent(sdlRenderer);                          // Update the screen with any rendering performed since the previous call
        }
    };
}
```

Your main game loop using this class might look something like this:

