### General Advice

- Make sure the event handling code is integrated into your main loop in such a way that it gets called each frame or when events are detected.
- Ensure that the state changes prompted by these events are handled in the appropriate parts of your code and that they trigger any necessary updates or redraws.
- Sometimes event handling code can become complex and convoluted as new features are added. You might consider separating event handling into different methods or classes to handle specific event types, especially if you find yourself dealing with many different event cases.

